				<a href="#scoring-winning-the-game" class="matrix-link">SCORING: WINNING THE GAME</a>
			</li>
        </ul>
    </nav>

    <!-- OBJECT -->
	<div id="object">
		<div class="rules-box">
			<h4>OBJECT</h4>
			<ul>
				<li>This game follows and enhances Cheat’s style of “Card Shedding” Play, therefore be the First Player to gid rid of their Cards.</li>
			</ul>
			<div class="return-link-wrapper">
				<a href="#top" class="return-link">🔝 Return to Rulebook Contents</a>
			</div>
		</div>
    </div>
	
    <!-- SETUP -->
	<div id="setup">
		<div class="rules-box">
			<h4>SETUP</h4>
			<ol>
				<li>As a group choose whether to use the Core Game Extension and any Optional Expansion or Coloured Extension Packs [compare Soloverse Game Notes: First Play Recommendations].
					<div class="note-box">NOTE: If you have added any Optional Expansions, check if they have any Additional Setup Rules.</div>
				</li>
				<li>Choose who Deals first [alternate the Dealer clockwise after each game].</li>
				<li>Shuffle the Deck and Deal 15 Cards to all Players.</li>
				<li>Then place the Deck in the middle of the Table, leaving room for the Discards to go beside it.</li>
				<li>Place the Direction Of Play [Blue/Clockwise Side] and the Play To The Side Of The Discards Chaos Cards Face-Up on either side of the Discards, where everyone can see them [Remember to Flip the Direction Of Play Chaos Card it every time a Reverse Effect Activates].</li>
				<li>If using the Core Extension, place Recycle Chaos Card Face-Up next to the Deck and Discards, where all Players can reach it.</li>
			</ol>
			<div class="return-link-wrapper">
				<a href="#top" class="return-link">🔝 Return to Rulebook Contents</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	
     <!-- HOW TO PLAY -->
	<div id="how-to-play">
		<div class="rules-box">
			<h4>HOW TO PLAY</h4>
			<ol>
				<li>On your turn, place Face-Down on the Discards [or beside them as the need arises] any of the following:
					<div class="note-box">NOTE: You do not have to tell the truth about Your Cards or Their Value.</div>
					<ol type="a">
						<li>One or more Same Valued Coloured Number Cards; then call out Their value and how many.
							<div class="important-box">IMPORTANT: The value of each set of declared Coloured Number Cards Played must be equal to, or sequentially higher than the last [i.e.: three 0’s, three 0’s, one 1’s, five 2’s, two 3’s].</div>
						</li>
						<li>Or an Action Class Card.
							<ol type="i">
								<li>Reverse.</li>
								<li>Skip.</li>
								<li>Draw +2.</li>
							</ol>
						</li>
						<li>Or a Powerful Chaos Card [according to its Entry in the Definitions Rulebook].</li>
					</ol>
				</li>
				<li>At any point, You can Challenge another Player by calling out “Cheat!”
				At which point that Player who put down must reveal their Card/s:
					<ol type="a">
						<li>If the Challenged Player was in fact Cheating, They must now pick up the entire Discards.</li>
						<li>If the Challenged Player was indeed telling the truth, the Challenging Player must pick up the entire Discards instead!</li>
					</ol>
					<div class="note-box">NOTE: If anyone Plays an Action Class Card or Chaos Card unchallenged, follow its Effects.</div>
				</li>
				<li>Cheating is allowed. But you will be penalised for getting caught.</li>
			</ol>
			<div class="return-link-wrapper">
				<a href="#top" class="return-link">🔝 Return to Rulebook Contents</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

     <!-- GOING OUT -->
	<div id="going-out">
		<div class="rules-box">
			<h4>GOING OUT</h4>
			<ol>
				<li>The first Player to get rid of all their Cards is the Winner!</li>
			</ol>
			<div class="return-link-wrapper">
				<a href="#top" class="return-link">🔝 Return to Rulebook Contents</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

    <!-- VICTORY CONDITIONS -->
	<div id="victory-conditions">
		<div class="rules-box">
			<h4>VICTORY CONDITIONS</h4>
			<ol>
				<li>Possessing no cards at the end of Your turn.
					<ul>
						<li>If at the end of Your turn You still have no Cards, the game ends and You are out of the Game.</li>
						<li>Points can be scored if desired [see: Scoring – Winning The Game], and Play can restart if desired.</li>
					</ul>
				</li>
				<li>If the last card Played in a round has a Draw Effect, continue Play until someone is forced to Draw cards.
					<ul>
						<li>Someone must Draw from the last Draw Effect Card. Until that happens, Your Win is not guaranteed...</li>
						<li>If You Play a Draw or Deal Effect Card as Your last Card and a Player/s Respond in Kind, and in doing so, brings the Draw or Deal Effect back to You, with nothing to defend Yourself with You must bear the consequences of the Draw or Deal Effect You initiated, cancelling Your Win.</li>
					</ul>
					<div class="note-box">NOTE: There is also the possibility of the Drawer obtaining Anti-Fun for example, that can still be used to negate Your win.</div>
				</li>
				<li>Special Victory Conditions.
					<ul>
						<li>Some Expansions have Special Victory Conditions that exceed the normal means of Winning. For example:</li>
							<ol type="a">
								<li>The Singularity Expansion allows You to collect all 3 Unification Class Chaos Cards.</li>
								<li>While the Crisis Expansion Crisis Class Chaos Cards allow for many different Special Victory Conditions.</li>
								<li>Finally, the Cataclysm Expansion allows You to collect all 6 Ancient Stone Class Chaos Cards.</li>
							</ol>
						<li>In any of these situations, doing so automatically, and instantly, Wins You the game!</li>
					</ul>
				</li>
				<li>The game ends Without a Clear Winner.
					<ol type="a">
						<li>As stated in Universal Game Notes: Important Notes: Rule 1, the Deck could run out of Drawable Cards.</li>
						<li>The Doomsday Expansion has the Soloversal Destruction Chaos Card that can cause Everyone to lose.</li>
						<li>In any situation without a clear Winner:
							<ul>
								<li>The Player with the least number of Cards Wins.
								If Scoring, do so normally [but do not count your own Cards].</li>
								<li>If more than one Player has equal Cards to Win, They Draw.
								If Scoring, count the other winning Player’s Cards as well [but not your own].</li>
							</ul>
						</li>
					</ol>
				</li>
			</ol>
			<div class="return-link-wrapper">
				<a href="#top" class="return-link">🔝 Return to Rulebook Contents</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

    <!-- TEAM GAMEPLAY -->
	<div id="team-gameplay">
		<div class="rules-box">
			<h4>TEAM GAMEPLAY</h4>
			<ol>
				<li>Make Teams with an even number of Members.</li>
				<li>Choose the Turn Order for Teams & Members [alternating Teams/Members between turns (e.g.: Team 1: Member 1, Team 2: Member 1, Team 1: Member 2, Team 2: Member 2, etc) ].</li>
				<li>Reorganise Seating arrangements to Match Team & Member Turns.</li>
				<li>Next, choose which Victory Condition to use before beginning play:
					<div class="advanced-box">OPTION 1: Relaxed:
						<ul>
							<li>The First Member to get rid of all their Cards wins for their Team.</li>
						</ul>
						<div class="note-box">NOTE: If Scoring, do not count your Team Member’s Cards.</div>
					</div>
					<div class="advanced-box">OPTION 2: Competitive:
						<ul>
							<li>The first Team with All Members to get rid of all their Cards Wins.</li>
						</ul>
						<div class="note-box">NOTES: Team Members with no Cards left can only be Group Targeted [e.g.: United We Fall]; this includes Group Targeting Trap Class Chaos Cards [e.g.: Epidemic from the Contagion Expansion]. Otherwise, Team Members with no Cards are Removed from the Game and have their Turns Automatically Skipped. If they receive Cards again, they are Re-added to the Game.</div>
					</div>
				</li>
				<li>Follow all other Game Rules.</li>
			</ol>
			<div class="return-link-wrapper">
				<a href="#top" class="return-link">🔝 Return to Rulebook Contents</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

    <!-- TEAM GAMEPLAY: TRADING -->
	<div id="team-trading">
		<div class="rules-box">
			<h4>TEAM TRADING</h4>
			<ol>
				<li>2 Team Members can Trade Cards [a free Card Swapping Effect] at a 1:1 Ratio on their Member Turn, by saying “Team Trade Requested.” However, this can only do so a minimum of once every 2 Team Turns, regardless of which Team Member took said Team Turns.</li>
				<li>All Card Types are allowed to be Traded during a Team Trade. This includes Trading for a Counter Class Chaos Card when facing Draw Effects [Stacked or otherwise].</li>
				<li>If there are more than 2 Players in a Team, the initiating Trader must designate which Team Member will participate.</li>
				<li>Discussion of which Cards are wanted to be received or be given in return is Forbidden. You must trust your Team Member to help however they can.</li>
				<li>Once a Team Trade is Requested, that 1:1 Trade Must be done [regardless of if the Traded Card would end up being helpful or not].</li>
				<li>Finally, a Team Member does not have to use the Card that was Traded to them on that Member’s Turn if they do not want to.</li>
			</ol>
			<div class="return-link-wrapper">
				<a href="#top" class="return-link">🔝 Return to Rulebook Contents</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>


    <!-- TEAM GAMEPLAY: SPECIAL VICTORY CONDITIONS -->
	<div id="team-special-victory-conditions-changes">
		<div class="rules-box">
			<h4>TEAM SPECIAL VICTORY CONDITIONS CHANGES</h4>
			<ul>
				<li>Singularity Expansion:
					<ul>
						<li>A Team wins if they possess all 3 Unification Class Chaos Cards between any of their Team Members.</li>
					</ul>
				</li>
				<li>Crisis Expansion:
					<ul>
						<li>Crisis Trap Class Chaos Cards are totalled for the Team.</li>
					</ul>
				</li>
				<li>Cataclysm Expansion:
					<ul>
						<li>The Bulk Possession Notes and Special Victory Condition are not shared across Team Members. However, on any Team Member’s Playable Turn, 1 Ancient Stone CAN be given to any other Team Member if all Team Members agree to Deal 5 Cards to themselves each [in play order]. Discussion of which Ancient Stone is given and who gets it is allowed by Team Members if it is kept brief.</li>
					</ul>
				</li>
			</ul>
			<div class="return-link-wrapper">
				<a href="#top" class="return-link">🔝 Return to Rulebook Contents</a>
			</div>
    	</div>
    </div>

    <!-- SCORING: WINNING THE GAME -->
	<div id="scoring-winning-the-game">
		<div class="rules-box">
			<h4>SCORING - WINNING THE GAME</h4>
			<ul>
				<li>If You feel up to it, mix things up by tracking Your progress by accumulating Your score as rounds progress.</li>
			</ul>
			<div class="advanced-box">LAST PLAYER STANDING: A Point is given for every Player left in the game when You go out.
				<ul>
					<li>The Last Player Standing has Points deducted based on the Number of other Players in the Game.</li>
				</ul>
				<div class="note-box">NOTE: Players cannot obtain a Negative Score.</div>
				<ul>
					<li>Play continues until a Player Scores the Required Total [the recommendation is 3 x the Number of Players in the game].</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div class="advanced-box">TOURNAMENT: The first Player to reach the above Point requirement earns 1 Credit. Rounds progress until one Player earns a total of 3 Credits [for the truly devoted, You could always agree to a larger figure ahead of Playing].</div>
			<div class="return-link-wrapper">
				<a href="#top" class="return-link">🔝 Return to Rulebook Contents</a>
			</div>
    	</div>
	</div>

	<!-- Soloverse Rulebook Page Engine: Auto-Theme Detection & Update Sync -->
    <script is:inline>
        (function() {
            // 1. SERVICE WORKER REVALIDATION
            if ('serviceWorker' in navigator) {
                navigator.serviceWorker.getRegistrations().then(function(registrations) {
                    for (let registration of registrations) {
                        registration.update(); 
                    }
                });
            }

            // 2. AUTOMATED THEME EVALUATION (User Override vs System Preference)
            const savedTheme = localStorage.getItem('soloverse-theme');
            const devicePrefersDarkMode = window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches;
            
            let activeTheme = 'dark'; // Base anchor default fallback

            if (savedTheme) {
                activeTheme = savedTheme;
            } else {
                activeTheme = devicePrefersDarkMode ? 'dark' : 'light';
            }

            // Mount theme instantly to root document element
            document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', activeTheme);
        })();
    </script>
</body>
</html>